"a.迷路的，误入歧途的 【英】 adj. 迷路的，误入歧途的( off the right path or way) 【记】 a+stray(走离)，stra y(走离，迷路)也是一 个单词 adj. 迷途的(偏离正确的道路或方向); 误入歧途的(走向错误和罪恶) 【例】The boy was led astray by bad companions 这小孩被坏伙伴诱入歧途. 【记】stray(v 迷路; adj 迷路的) 【记】a + stray 无目的方向的走,迷路,偏离；a 无 + street 无路走→迷路；音：我死追，我死命追坏人，结果迷路 astray (adv.)  c.1300, astraied ""away from home; lost,"" borrowed and partially nativized from Old French estraie, past participle of estraier ""astray, riderless (of a horse), lost,"" literally ""on stray"" (see stray (v.))."
